   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Step 1: Informatics-Standard ML Pipeline\n",
    "This notebook implements the **Gold Standard** informatics workflow. It focuses on:\n",
    "1. **Feature Alignment:** Finding common genes across platforms.\n",
    "2. **Data Leakage Prevention:** Using Scikit-Learn Pipelines.\n",
    "3. **Robust Serialization:** Saving the entire preprocessing and model chain.\n",
    "4. **Statistical Rigor:** Calculating 95% Confidence Intervals using bootstrap."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "93d00679",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import joblib\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, f_classif\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_validate, StratifiedKFold\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import make_scorer, roc_auc_score, recall_score, confusion_matrix, precision_recall_curve, auc, balanced_accuracy_score, precision_score, f1_score, matthews_corrcoef, brier_score_loss\\n",\n    "from sklearn.calibration import calibration_curve\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "def pr_auc_score(y_true, y_probs):\\n",\n    "    precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_true, y_probs)\\n",\n    "    return auc(recall, precision)\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "def process_geo_data(matrix_file, annotation_file, data_dir=\\"../raw_data\\"):\\n",\n    "    m_path = os.path.join(data_dir, matrix_file)\\n",\n    "    a_path = os.path.join(data_dir, annotation_file)\\n",\n    "    \\n",\n    "    expr = pd.read_csv(m_path, sep=\\"\\\\t\\", comment=\\"!\\", low_memory=False)\\n",\n    "    expr.iloc[:, 1:] = expr.iloc[:, 1:].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors=\\"coerce\\")\\n",\n    "    \\n",\n    "    gpl = pd.read_csv(a_path, sep=\\"\\\\t\\", comment=\\"#\\", low_memory=False)\\n",\n    "    gpl_clean = gpl[[\\"ID\\", \\"Gene Symbol\\"]].dropna()\\n",\n    "    gpl_clean = gpl_clean[gpl_clean[\\"Gene Symbol\\"] != \\"---\\"]\\n",\n    "    \\n",\n    "    merged = expr.merge(gpl_clean, left_on=\\"ID_REF\\", right_on=\\"ID\\")\\n",\n    "    merged[\\"Gene Symbol\\"] = merged[\\"Gene Symbol\\"].astype(str).str.split(\\"///\\").str[0].str.strip()\\n",\n    "    \\n",\n    "    gene_expr = merged.groupby(\\"Gene Symbol\\").mean(numeric_only=True)\\n",\n    "    return gene_expr.T\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "def bootstrap_metrics(y_true, y_probs, y_pred, n_bootstraps=1000):\\n",\n    "    rng = np.random.RandomState(42)\\n",\n    "    metrics = {\\n",\n    "        'auc': [], 'pr_auc': [], 'sens': [], 'spec': [], \\n",    "        'balanced_acc': [], 'precision': [], 'f1': [], 'mcc': [], 'brier': []\\n",    "    }\\n",\n    "    \\n",\n    "    for i in range(n_bootstraps):\\n",\n    "        indices = rng.randint(0, len(y_true), len(y_true))\\n",\n    "        if len(np.unique(y_true[indices])) < 2:\\n",\n    "            continue\\n",\n    "            \\n",\n    "        y_true_b, y_probs_b, y_pred_b = y_true[indices], y_probs[indices], y_pred[indices]\\n",\n    "        \\n",\n    "        metrics['auc'].append(roc_auc_score(y_true_b, y_probs_b))\\n",\n    "        metrics['pr_auc'].append(pr_auc_score(y_true_b, y_probs_b))\\n",\n    "        \\n",\n    "        tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_true_b, y_pred_b, labels=[0, 1]).ravel()\\n",\n    "        metrics['sens'].append(tp / (tp + fn) if (tp + fn) > 0 else 0)\\n",\n    "        metrics['spec'].append(tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) > 0 else 0)\\n",\n    "        \\n",\n    "        metrics['balanced_acc'].append(balanced_accuracy_score(y_true_b, y_pred_b))\\n",\n    "        metrics['precision'].append(precision_score(y_true_b, y_pred_b, zero_division=0))\\n",\n    "        metrics['f1'].append(f1_score(y_true_b, y_pred_b, zero_division=0))\\n",\n    "        metrics['mcc'].append(matthews_corrcoef(y_true_b, y_pred_b))\\n",\n    "        metrics['brier'].append(brier_score_loss(y_true_b, y_probs_b))\\n",\n    "        \\n",\n    "    return metrics,\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "def get_ci(data):\\n",\n    "    if len(data) == 0: return (0, 0)\\n",\n    "    sorted_data = np.sort(data)\\n",\n    "    lower = sorted_data[int(0.025 * len(sorted_data))]\\n",\n    "    upper = sorted_data[int(0.975 * len(sorted_data))]\\n",\n    "    return lower, upper"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c7b26b5b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. Data Alignment\n",
    "We load training (GSE42568) and validation (GSE15852) sets and find common genes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "be9acf5d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_train_raw = process_geo_data(\"GSE42568_series_matrix.txt\", \"GPL570-55999.txt\")\n",
    "y_train = np.array([1]*104 + [0]*17)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_test_raw = process_geo_data(\"GSE15852_series_matrix.txt\", \"GPL96-57554.txt\")\n",
    "y_test = np.array([1]*43 + [0]*43)\n",
    "\n",
    "common_genes = X_train_raw.columns.intersection(X_test_raw.columns)\n",
    "X_train = X_train_raw[common_genes]\n",
    "X_test = X_test_raw[common_genes]\n",
    "print(f\"Features aligned: {len(common_genes)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7b702385",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. The Unified Pipeline and Cross-Validation\n",\n    "#### Data Leakage Prevention Audit\n",\n    "To ensure no information from the test set (or validation folds) influences the training process, we utilize Scikit-Learn **Pipelines**. This architecture guarantees:\n",\n    "1. **Scaling (StandardScaler)**: Means and standard deviations are computed strictly on the training folds and applied to test folds.\n",\n    "2. **Feature Selection (SelectKBest)**: Feature rankings and selection are performed inside each cross-validation fold. Features are never selected on the full dataset before splitting.\n",\n    "3. **Model Training**: The classifier is blind to test set labels until the final evaluation step.\n",\n    "\n",\n    "This nested architecture (Outer CV: Generalization, Inner Pipeline: Feature/Scale selection) is a fundamental requirement for informatics rigor."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1f9f3608",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pipe = Pipeline([\n",
    "    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),\n",
    "    ('selector', SelectKBest(score_func=f_classif, k=500)),\n",
    "    ('classifier', SVC(kernel='linear', class_weight='balanced', probability=True, random_state=42))\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "scoring = {\\n",\n    "    'roc_auc': 'roc_auc', \\n",\n    "    'pr_auc': make_scorer(pr_auc_score, needs_proba=True), \\n",\n    "    'accuracy': 'accuracy', \\n",\n    "    'balanced_accuracy': 'balanced_accuracy',\\n",\n    "    'f1': 'f1',\\n",\n    "    'precision': 'precision',\\n",\n    "    'mcc': make_scorer(matthews_corrcoef),\\n",\n    "    'sensitivity': 'recall', \\n",\n    "    'specificity': make_scorer(recall_score, pos_label=0)\\n",\n    "}\\n",\n    "cv_results = cross_validate(pipe, X_train, y_train, cv=StratifiedKFold(5), scoring=scoring)\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "print(\\"=== 5-Fold Stratified Cross-Validation Results ===\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Mean ROC-AUC: {cv_results['test_roc_auc'].mean():.4f} (+/- {cv_results['test_roc_auc'].std():.4f})\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Mean Balanced Acc: {cv_results['test_balanced_accuracy'].mean():.4f} (+/- {cv_results['test_balanced_accuracy'].std():.4f})\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Mean MCC: {cv_results['test_mcc'].mean():.4f} (+/- {cv_results['test_mcc'].std():.4f})\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Mean F1-score: {cv_results['test_f1'].mean():.4f} (+/- {cv_results['test_f1'].std():.4f})\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Mean Sensitivity: {cv_results['test_sensitivity'].mean():.4f} (+/- {cv_results['test_sensitivity'].std():.4f})\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Mean Specificity: {cv_results['test_specificity'].mean():.4f} (+/- {cv_results['test_specificity'].std():.4f})\\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dc0ec35f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. External Validation with Confidence Intervals\n",
    "We train on the full training set and evaluate on the independent external validation set, providing 95% CIs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a9d94221",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pipe.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "y_probs = pipe.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]\n",
    "y_pred = pipe.predict(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "auc_val = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_probs)\\n",\n    "bacc_val = balanced_accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\\n",\n    "mcc_val = matthews_corrcoef(y_test, y_pred)\\n",\n    "brier_val = brier_score_loss(y_test, y_probs)\\n",\n    "tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred).ravel()\\n",\n    "sens_val = tp / (tp + fn)\\n",\n    "spec_val = tn / (tn + fp)\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "print(\\"=== External Validation Results ===\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"ROC-AUC: {auc_val:.4f}\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Balanced Accuracy: {bacc_val:.4f}\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"MCC: {mcc_val:.4f}\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Brier Score: {brier_val:.4f}\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Sensitivity: {sens_val:.4f}\\")\\n",\n    "print(f\\"Specificity: {spec_val:.4f}\\")\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "print(\\"\\\\nCalculating 95% Confidence Intervals (Bootstrap, n=1000)...\\")\\n",\n    "metrics_b, = bootstrap_metrics(y_test, y_probs, y_pred)\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "for m_name in metrics_b:\\n",\n    "    ci = get_ci(metrics_b[m_name])\\n",\n    "    print(f\\"{m_name.upper()} 95% CI: [{ci[0]:.4f}, {ci[1]:.4f}]\\")"
    "\n",
    "os.makedirs(\"../models\", exist_ok=True)\n",
    "    "joblib.dump(pipe, \\"../models/breast_cancer_pipeline_v1.pkl\\")\\n",\n    "print(\\"\\\\nPipeline Serialized Successfully.\\")"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "calibration_section",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "### 4. Calibration Analysis\\n",\n    "Calibration evaluates how well the predicted probabilities match observed frequencies. A Calibration Slope of 1.0 is ideal."\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "calibration_impl",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "prob_true, prob_pred = calibration_curve(y_test, y_probs, n_bins=5)\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "# Calculate Calibration Slope using Logistic Regression on Logits\\n",\n    "logits = np.log(y_probs / (1 - y_probs))\\n",\n    "calib_model = LogisticRegression()\\n",\n    "calib_model.fit(logits.reshape(-1, 1), y_test)\\n",\n    "slope = calib_model.coef_[0][0]\\n",\n    "\\n",\n    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\\n",\n    "plt.plot(prob_pred, prob_true, marker='o', label=f'SVM (Slope: {slope:.2f})')\\n",\n    "plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle='--', color='gray', label='Perfectly Calibrated')\\n",\n    "plt.xlabel(\"Mean Predicted Probability\")\\n",\n    "plt.ylabel(\"Fraction of Positives\")\\n",\n    "plt.title(\"Calibration Curve\")\\n",\n    \"plt.legend()\\n\",\n    \"plt.grid(alpha=0.3)\\n\",\n    \"plt.savefig(\\\"../figures/Figure_10_Calibration_Curve.jpeg\\\", dpi=300)\\n\",\n    \"plt.show()\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"print(f\\\"Calibration Slope: {slope:.4f}\\\")\"\n   ]\n  } \n ],
 "metadata": {
